<p> 
Our smart classifier works by applying a technique similar to that of spam and anti-malware filters in detecting messages that are likely to be harmful or dangerous. </p>

<p>By applying a mathematical algorithm to the content of a message we are able to generate a rating for each item regarding the probability that it is of a bullying or other harmful nature.
</p>

<p> 
Our service allows a parent or guardian to agree with their minor which elements the service will monitor for and automatically sends a summary of potentially suspicious messages for them both review. 
</p>

<p> 
<b>These summary messages only include: </b>
<ul>
    <li>Sender name</li>
<li>Number of suspicious messages</li>
<li>Categories the classifier flagged the messages for</li>
</ul>
<b>No message content is ever shared with the parent or guardian.</b>
</p>

<p> 
To stop the messages from being flagged, both the parent and minor must agree or disagree with the classification of messages for them to stop being flagged from that user in future.

</p>
      </div>
